1. Install NodeJS
2. Install Java SE and Java RE
3. Set JAVA_HOME and JRE_HOME variables in the PATH
4. Create new project
5. Type in the console npm init (set all needed information)
6. Type in teh console npm install webdriverio --save-dev
7. Type in the console npm test (set test folder ./test/**/*.js)
8. Create test folder in the root of the project.


Troubleshooting:
1) problem with selenium selenium-standalone server
In the root folder "npm install selenium-standalone"
Navigate to the node_modules/.bin and execute command "selenium-standalone install"
